      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo, i'm stuck on this problem from a contest. the constraints are super tight and i keep getting MLE (Memory Limit Exceeded). it's a graph problem on a huge grid with weights.\n\nproblem: find the shortest path in an N x M grid where N, M <= 5000, but there are 'special' nodes that connect to many others. the memory limit is only 64MB. i tried a standard Dijkstra with an adjacency list and a distance array but it just crashes immediately. \n\ni just need a solution that passes the hidden test cases without hitting that memory cap. can u help me write the python code for this? i'll provide the sample input if u need it.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
